Inspired by the intersection between Bayesian inference and infinite-dimensional optimization problems exposed by Zellner (1988) and Bissiri, Holmes & Walker (2016), this project aims at extending the flexibility and customizeability of Bayesian inference. The first stepping stone on this path is [Generalized Variational Inference (GVI)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.02063 "Link to GVI paper"). GVI is based on a generalized representation of Bayesian inference that I believe can inspire further methodological advances. As we have shown, this approach is remarkably powerful: See [here](https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.02303 "Link to Robust DGP paper") for an application to Deep Gaussian Processes and [here](https://arxiv.org/abs/1806.02261 "Link to Robust BOCPD paper") for an application to Bayesian On-line Changepoint Detection. Code for each of the projects is linked within the papers.
